Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. What colour was it? A. Black. I had been to Holborn, to a singing party; I had drank something;
Emma Weightman
was with me, and was as sober as I was; I did not see who took it; I had passed the evening at the King's Arms, between Hatton-garden and Ely-place; we had had three sixpenny glasses of gin and water - it was the first day of the Fair.



      THOMAS 
      HAMMOND




. I took the prisoner. She gave me a direction to Leather-lane, where I found there had been a suit of clothes pawned but they had been redeemed;
